cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.SI 

This paper uses computer vision techniques to analyze satellite imagery to predict poverty levels in Uganda. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses machine learning algorithms to analyze the data, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses feature importance and ablation analysis, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with geographic data, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics).
